article.description: Jeremy Hollowell made a career-high six 3-pointers and scored 22 points, Isaiah Williams added three 3s and 19 points, and Georgia State beat Wright State 81-74 on Wednesday night.
article.headline: Hollowell hits 6 3s, Georgia State beats Wright State 81-74
article.linkText: Hollowell hits 6 3s, Georgia State beats Wright State 81-74
article.story: ATLANTA -- Jeremy Hollowell made a career-high six 3-pointers and scored 22 points, Isaiah Williams added three 3s and 19 points, and Georgia State beat Wright State 81-74 on Wednesday night. Hollowell scored 20-plus for the third time this season and finished 8 of 14 from the field, including 6 of 11 from distance. He and Williams combined for nine of Georgia State's 11 3-pointers. Wright State trailed by as many as 24 in the second half, but cut it to five with just over a minute to play. But Williams answered with a jumper and he made two free throws on Georgia State's next possession for a nine-point lead. Georgia State (4-2) made just 18 of 30 free-throw attempts. Grant Benzinger led Wright State (6-2) with 32 points and eight rebounds. He was 9 of 18 from the field, including 6 of 12 from 3-point range. Mark Alstork added 19 points and eight rebounds. Both head coaches went barefoot to raise awareness for Samaritan's Feet.
